---
---

<div class="gradient-divider"></div>
<section class="relative py-24 md:py-32">
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6">
    <div class="mb-16 reveal">
      <p class="font-mono text-[12px] text-electric-400 uppercase tracking-[0.3em] mb-4">The business case</p>
      <h2 class="font-display text-[clamp(1.75rem,4vw,3rem)] font-bold tracking-[-0.02em] max-w-2xl leading-[1.15]">
        AI investment you can <span class="gradient-text">measure.</span>
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-white/50 text-[17px] leading-relaxed max-w-xl">
        ROI, visibility, and adoption — not as promises, but as outputs you can observe.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-12">
      <!-- Card 1: Cost reduction -->
      <div class="p-8 rounded-2xl border border-electric-500/20 bg-electric-500/[0.03] reveal">
        <p class="font-mono text-[11px] text-electric-400 uppercase tracking-[0.25em] mb-4">Cost reduction</p>
        <p class="font-display text-[3rem] font-bold tracking-[-0.03em] leading-none mb-3 gradient-text">~51%</p>
        <p class="font-display text-[1.1rem] font-semibold text-white mb-3 leading-snug">Model routing savings</p>
        <p class="text-white/45 text-[15px] leading-relaxed">
          Routine tasks don't need the most expensive model. The system picks automatically — we cut our own AI bill in half through dogfooding.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Card 2: Pipeline visibility -->
      <div class="p-8 rounded-2xl border border-white/[0.06] bg-white/[0.02] reveal">
        <p class="font-mono text-[11px] text-white/30 uppercase tracking-[0.25em] mb-4">Pipeline visibility</p>
        <p class="font-display text-[1.6rem] font-bold tracking-[-0.02em] leading-tight text-white mb-3">See what your AI investment actually produces.</p>
        <p class="text-white/45 text-[15px] leading-relaxed">
          Fix-cascade rates, first-time quality scores, CI pass rates — metrics that map AI activity to engineering outcomes, not token counts.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Card 3: Adoption -->
      <div class="p-8 rounded-2xl border border-white/[0.06] bg-white/[0.02] reveal">
        <p class="font-mono text-[11px] text-white/30 uppercase tracking-[0.25em] mb-4">Adoption</p>
        <p class="font-display text-[1.6rem] font-bold tracking-[-0.02em] leading-tight text-white mb-3">Embedded in the pipeline, not left to habit.</p>
        <p class="text-white/45 text-[15px] leading-relaxed">
          Adoption isn't individual — it's structural. When AI assistance is part of the workflow itself, usage is consistent across the whole team.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="reveal">
      <a
        href="https://proof.shipwrightharness.com/public/dashboard"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-[15px] text-electric-400 hover:text-electric-300 transition-colors duration-200 font-medium"
      >
        See the live numbers
        <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M13.5 4.5L21 12m0 0l-7.5 7.5M21 12H3" />
        </svg>
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
